The course will focus on gradation, its categories, their determination, basic concepts of morphology, parts of Estonian speech, their determination, the principles of classifying words into inflection types, cases of Estonian language, their formation, declension types of Estonian language, declination of nouns, comparison of adjectives, their formation, forms of verbs, their formation, differentia and terminations, conjugation types of Estonian language, conjugation of verbs. The course expands upon these concepts and subject fields with special emphasis on the formation of practical skills and proficiency.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give a systematic overview of the morphological structure and classification of Estonian language. To embed the implementation skills of obtained knowledge.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course knows basic concepts of morphology, systems of gradation and declension-conjugation types of Estonian language; is able to 1) describe and analyze the morphological structure of Estonian language, 2) employ the acquired skills in practical works.
